label: Age Group
desc: Subject Age Group (10 year increments) as reported by the officer.

label: Subject Key
desc: Key, generated daily, identifying unique subjects in the dataset using a character to character match of first name and last name. "Null" values indicate an "anonymous" or "unidentified" subject. Subjects of a Terry Stop are not required to present identification.

label: Offense Number
desc: General Offense or Street Check number, relating the Terry Stop to the parent report. This field may have a one to many relationship in the data.

label: Terry Stop Key
desc: Key identifying unique Terry Stop reports.

label: Stop Resolution
desc: Resolution of the stop as reported by the officer.

label: Weapon Type
desc: Type of weapon, if any, identified during a search or frisk of the subject. Indicates "None" if no weapons was found.

label: Officer Key
desc: Key identifying unique officers in the dataset.

label: Officer Birth Year
desc: Year of birth, as reported by the officer.

label: Officer Gender
desc: Gender of the officer, as reported by the officer.

label: Officer Race
desc: Race of the officer, as reported by the officer.

label: Subject Race
desc: Perceived race of the subject, as reported by the officer.

label: Subject Gender
desc: Perceived gender of the subject, as reported by the officer.

label: Report Date
desc: Date the report was filed in the Records Management System (RMS). Not necessarily the date the stop occurred but generally within 1 day.

label: Report Time
desc: Time the stop was reported in the Records Management System (RMS). Not the time the stop occurred but generally within 10 hours.

label: Initial Call Type
desc: Initial classification of the call as assigned by 911.

label: Final Call Type
desc: Final classification of the call as assigned by the primary officer closing the event.

label: Call Receipt
desc: How the call was received by the communication center.

label: Squad Assignment
desc: Functional squad assignment (not budget) of the officer as reported by the Data Analytics Platform (DAP).

label: Arrest Made
desc: Indicator of whether a "physical arrest" was made, of the subject, during the Terry Stop. Does not necessarily reflect a report of an arrest in the Records Management System (RMS).

label: Frisk Conducted
desc: Indicator of whether a "frisk" was conducted, by the officer, of the subject, during the Terry Stop.

label: Precinct
desc: Precinct of the address associated with the underlying Computer Aided Dispatch (CAD) event. Not necessarily where the Terry Stop occurred.

label: Sector
desc: Sector of the address associated with the underlying Computer Aided Dispatch (CAD) event. Not necessarily where the Terry Stop occurred.

label: Beat
desc: Beat of the address associated with the underlying Computer Aided Dispatch (CAD) event. Not necessarily where the Terry Stop occurred.
